_decoded_content.name: robotic hand servo controlled fingers
_decoded_content.description:
Servo controlled  hand.
By flexing the elbow the hand will close. 
The servos are controlled by a servo testing unit, so no need for arduino sketch etc.
The fingers hinges are connected with ptfe tube 4mm, and the small rods are fastened with petg 1.75. 

The servo test unit box is a remix from Alex Sahka  (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:35515). And the gears to move the knob for motion control are remix from elefantman (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:683389).
For powering the servos and testbox i used the 4 AA battery holder by devlab (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:35515) this file is included.

The upper and lower arm piece are printed flat, and need some thermofolding. They were inspired by another arm design uploaded by laurah (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2066705)

3 servo MG90s
servo testing box 
PTFE tube

I will upload the final BOM and building instructions.
If parts are changed i will make a notification of the uploaded/changed part.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZhDsKN0UFYg

------UPDATE-------
If you want to print this project, but you have already made my other hand https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2171811/#files. You can use that hand for this project. Just need to print the wrist adaptor. This makes it compatible with the lower arm from this project.

_decoded_content.details:
Summary

Servo controlled hand.
By flexing the elbow the hand will close.
The servos are controlled by a servo testing unit, so no need for arduino sketch etc.
The fingers hinges are connected with ptfe tube 4mm, and the small rods are fastened with petg 1.75.

The servo test unit box is a remix from Alex Sahka (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:35515). And the gears to move the knob for motion control are remix from elefantman (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:683389).
For powering the servos and testbox i used the 4 AA battery holder by devlab (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:35515) this file is included.

The upper and lower arm piece are printed flat, and need some thermofolding. They were inspired by another arm design uploaded by laurah (https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2066705)

3 servo MG90s
servo testing box
PTFE tube

I will upload the final BOM and building instructions.
If parts are changed i will make a notification of the uploaded/changed part.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZhDsKN0UFYg

------UPDATE-------
If you want to print this project, but you have already made my other hand https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2171811/#files. You can use that hand for this project. Just need to print the wrist adaptor. This makes it compatible with the lower arm from this project.

Post-Printing

1
Print all the parts.
Fingers need to printed 5 times.
Connector rod 3_5 needs to be printed 10 times
Connector rod 1_2 needs to be printed 5 times

2
Hand plate has a bending guide in the middle. Heat the plate with a heat gun. Just enough to make it flex. Bend the hand plate, so it’s become concave.
Make sure the hinge parts are perpendicular. If not push a 4mm rod through the holes. And use washers and nuts to help you make it perpendicular. Make the parts flexible with the heat gun (not to hot) and just tighten the nuts.

3
Fingers parts are connected with a 4mm PTFE tube. Drill the outer holes with a 4mm drill, and the inner holes with a 4,2 or 4.5 drill. So the inner part can move free on the PTFE tube. But has a snug fit on the outer parts
The finger connector parts (connector 1_2 and 3_5) are connected using some filament. Just push the filament through the holes, and use a lighter or welding torch to meld the filament so it locks the parts

4
The fingers are placed on the hand plate and use some screws to fasten them.

5
The upper and lower arm need to be thermoformed. First heat up the part, but be careful at the hinge parts. Better to do this multiple times so you can make little adjustments.
The hinges need to be perpendicular. So use a 4mm rod as used by the hand parts. Make sure that you do this for both hinges at the lower arm part. Then heat up the lower arm, just the middle. And rotate the arm. So the elbow and wrist part are 90 dgs rotated in opposite of each other.

6
The servo test unit needs to be taken out of its cover. Just remove the plastic. And place the servo test unit on the bottom part. And when top part is placed use screws to clap the parts together.
The servo test knob is replaced with a gear. I used the 22 teeth and the 52 teeth version. If you want to change the range of motion for the servo control, you can use other gear versions https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:683389.

7
The battery box mockup is explained here https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:35515
